    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Future Trends in Ventilated Totes</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">As the Canadian produce export industry continues to evolve, several trends are shaping the future of ventilated totes:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-gray-700 mb-10">
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Smart Packaging</span>: Integration of temperature or humidity sensors to monitor produce condition during transport.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Lightweight, Durable Materials</span>: New plastics and composites reduce weight while maintaining strength.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Customization</span>: Tailored tote designs for specific crops, stacking requirements, and transport systems.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Automation-Friendly</span>: Totes designed to integrate with automated sorting, packing, and warehouse handling systems.</li>
      <li><span class="font-semibold">Eco-Friendly Manufacturing</span>: Recyclable or biodegradable plastics reduce environmental impact while maintaining durability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">For Canadian produce exporters, ventilated totes are more than just storage containers—they are essential tools for protecting crops, maintaining freshness, reducing waste, and supporting sustainability. Pacific Injection Molding’s range of ventilated totes is designed to meet the unique challenges faced by BC growers and exporters, providing durability, ergonomic design, stackability, and proper ventilation for a variety of crops.</p>
